Reasoning: 
1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The problem of finding the minimum dimension d such that a graph can be embedded into the integer lattice is a problem in discrete mathematics, and this category covers topics related to graph theory and combinatorics. 
2. cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The problem of isometrically embedding a graph into a lattice can be seen as a problem in computational geometry, as it involves finding a geometric representation of the graph. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper describes a polynomial time algorithm for the problem, which falls under the scope of this category. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The problem of embedding a graph into a lattice can also be seen as a numerical problem, as it involves finding a solution that satisfies certain constraints. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the problem and provides an algorithm with polynomial time complexity, which falls under the scope of this category.
